INSERT INTO `couch_data_text` VALUES("10", "106", "<article class=\"story\" id=\"story-2\" name=\"story-2\">\r\n	<h4>\r\n		From one heart to another - <em>Julia, 2nd grade</em></h4>\r\n	<p>\r\n		Julia was referred to our counseling team by her mom and teacher who were both concerned about her self- esteem. Julia has ADHD and struggles with impulse control, which can make it hard to learn, and hard to make friends. She had fallen behind academically and socially, and at her first meeting with her therapist cried in her office asking: &quot;Why is it so much harder for me to make a friend than everyone else?&quot;</p>\r\n	<p class=\"quote-text\">\r\n		&nbsp;</p>\r\n	<blockquote class=\"quote-right\">\r\n		On her own she recognized her distress, gave her lots of encouragement, and helped her problem solve.</blockquote>\r\n	For six months Julia and her therapist worked on friendship skills, identifying her strengths and helping her learn to think positive thoughts about herself. She is attending a summer social skills camp at a Tukwila elementary school, and has quickly formed a bond with another girl who has similar difficulties. In fact on the first day of &quot;RAYS Camp&quot;, Julia showed remarkable empathy when her new friend became frustrated during an art activity. On her own she recognized her distress, gave her lots of encouragement, and helped her problem solve. Her therapist remarked that &quot;Julia has the biggest heart I&#39;ve ever encountered in such a young person, and it was a thrill to see her use some of the skills we&#39;ve been practicing to help a friend. &quot;\r\n	<p>\r\n		&nbsp;</p>\r\n</article>\r\n", "From one heart to another - Julia, 2nd grade Julia was referred to our counseling team by her mom and teacher who were both concerned about her self- esteem. Julia has ADHD and struggles with impulse control, which can make it hard to learn, and hard to make friends. She had fallen behind academically and socially, and at her first meeting with her therapist cried in her office asking: &quot;Why is it so much harder for me to make a friend than everyone else?&quot;  On her own she recognized her distress, gave her lots of encouragement, and helped her problem solve. For six months Julia and her therapist worked on friendship skills, identifying her strengths and helping her learn to think positive thoughts about herself. She is attending a summer social skills camp at a Tukwila elementary school, and has quickly formed a bond with another girl who has similar difficulties. In fact on the first day of &quot;RAYS Camp&quot;, Julia showed remarkable empathy when her new friend became frustrated during an art activity. On her own she recognized her distress, gave her lots of encouragement, and helped her problem solve. Her therapist remarked that &quot;Julia has the biggest heart I&#039;ve ever encountered in such a young person, and it was a thrill to see her use some of the skills we&#039;ve been practicing to help a friend. &quot; ");
INSERT INTO `couch_data_text` VALUES("10", "107", "<p>\r\n	For more than 40 years RAYS has worked with youth and their families to overcome challenges, build healthier habits, and more beneficial relationships. Through one-on- one counseling, or communication with the whole family, RAYS helps its clients build the capacity to improve their own circumstances. We believe in a hollistic approach considering the needs of all members of the family, while never forgetting that it is the child-caregiver relationship that is our primary client. We believe that everyone can recover, if they are just have the tools to do so.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	At RAYS we celebrate both small and large victories alike, because change can be difficult. RAYS serves primarily high- needs families, and provides referrals to other services and organizations when they are needed. By building skills that help today, we believe that our communities will be stronger tomorrow.</p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	Our expertise</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	RAYS has extensive experience in working with people of extremely diverse circumstances and cultural backgrounds. We&#39;ve worked with all kinds of familial situations, including foster families, grandparents raising grandchildren, and homes of relative placements. Our staff includes master&#39;s level trained therapists and bachelor&#39;s level trained case managers with significant experience with a broad range of issues including, but not limited to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Behavioral problems</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Anger management</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Domestic violence &amp; child abuse</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Child abuse prevention</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Depression</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Grief &amp; loss</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>\r\n	Our services</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	RAYS works closely with families and communities to build on strengths and improve the emotional and behavioral health of youth of all ages, in a wide variety of settings.</p>\r\n", "For more than 40 years RAYS has worked with youth and their families to overcome challenges, build healthier habits, and more beneficial relationships. Through one-on- one counseling, or communication with the whole family, RAYS helps its clients build the capacity to improve their own circumstances. We believe in a hollistic approach considering the needs of all members of the family, while never forgetting that it is the child-caregiver relationship that is our primary client. We believe that everyone can recover, if they are just have the tools to do so. At RAYS we celebrate both small and large victories alike, because change can be difficult. RAYS serves primarily high- needs families, and provides referrals to other services and organizations when they are needed. By building skills that help today, we believe that our communities will be stronger tomorrow. Our expertise RAYS has extensive experience in working with people of extremely diverse circumstances and cultural backgrounds. We&#039;ve worked with all kinds of familial situations, including foster families, grandparents raising grandchildren, and homes of relative placements. Our staff includes master&#039;s level trained therapists and bachelor&#039;s level trained case managers with significant experience with a broad range of issues including, but not limited to: Behavioral problems Anger management Domestic violence &amp; child abuse Child abuse prevention Depression Grief &amp; loss Our services RAYS works closely with families and communities to build on strengths and improve the emotional and behavioral health of youth of all ages, in a wide variety of settings.");
