INSERT INTO `couch_fulltext` VALUES("18", "Default page for work.php * PLEASE CHANGE THIS TITLE *", "Internships Child &amp; Family Therapists / Case Managers / Youth Life Coaches RAYS offers internship opportunities with a paid stipend for students who are enrolled in accredited university programs. Both master&#039;s level and bachelor&#039;s level students receive regular individual supervision. All internship experiences will likely include providing services both agency-based and within our school-based services program. Internships offered include the following: Child and Family Therapist Intern (master&#039;s level), Case Manager Intern (bachelor&#039;s level), Youth Life Coach (bachelor&#039;s level). All experiences may include providing a combination of individual, family, and group services. To apply please send a cover letter and resume to: RAYS Attn. HR  web 1025 South Third Street Renton, WA 98057 Fax: 425-227-8926 RAYS can utilize volunteers in a number of differnet capacities, depending on current needs and the time of year. If you&#039;re interested in volunteering with us, please give us a call at 425-271-5600. ");
INSERT INTO `couch_fulltext` VALUES("19", "Default page for sparkthis.php * PLEASE CHANGE THIS TITLE *", "Spark T.H.I.S. students and staff participate in the Martin Luther King, Jr. Day march in Seattle, January 2013. Spark T.H.I.S. students and staff enjoy an afternoon of Kayaking with the Mountaineers on Lake Washington, July 2013. Spark T.H.I.S. students volunteer with the American Red Cross, while learning about emergency care &amp; services, April 2013. Spark T.H.I.S. students relax at the top of the wall after climbing with the Mountaineers, September 2012. Truth, Hope, Involvement, Success Our mission Spark T.H.I.S. promotes student success in school and in the community by providing one-on-one coaching, group support, and skill building opportunities for middle and high school youth, with a high quality programming standard. What we do We work within the Renton School District, building on resources provided by teachers, school counselors and other school staff. We believe that good relationships with school staff are essential to maximizing students opportunities to succeed in school. We believe that family members can and should play a key role in their children&#039;s school success, and so we try to engage families whenever possible. If a supportive adult family member is not available, we will work with the youth to identify and establish a strong relationship with a supportive adult outside the family. We believe that diversity enriches the school environment, and so we help youth to celebrate and appreciate diversity, and their own unique heritage. Youth connections with the school (and greater) community contribute to staying in school and ultimately graduating. We work with youth to increase participation in school and extracurricular activities, along with community volunteer work. How we do it ");
